text: Ruby, my Garmin is showing high intensity minutes even on rest days. Feeling lightheaded when standing.
Thanks, Rohan. Flagging to Dr. Warren as Priority 1. Any shortness of breath or chest pain?
No chest pain. Some dizziness on standing.
Likely autonomic imbalance. Ordering baseline panel + ECG. Please share prior records.
decision_rationale: Rule out anemia, thyroid, electrolyte disturbances; assess inflammation & cardiometabolic risk.

text: Booked tests at Raffles Medical, Singapore for Jan 18, 8:30 AM. Calendar invite sent to Sarah.
Results: LDL-C 142 mg/dL, ApoB 104 mg/dL, hs-CRP 2.1 mg/L, fasting glucose 96 mg/dL, OGTT normal, ECG normal. BP averages 132/84. Family history noted.
Decision: start 8-week lifestyle-first protocol; defer statin for now. Add Omega-3 (2 g/day EPA+DHA) and 4-week recheck lipids.
decision_rationale: Borderline-high ApoB with family history; trial lifestyle + omega-3 before pharmacotherapy.

text: Fuel plan v1: 30% protein, 40% complex carbs, 30% fats; fiber ≥35g; reduce refined snacks during travel. Chef brief attached.
decision_rationale: Increase satiety, support lipid lowering and cognitive performance.

text: Chassis plan v1: 2x/wk strength (45m), 1x zone-2 (40–50m), 1x mobility (20m). Progress every 2 weeks. Form videos requested.
decision_rationale: Support BP, HRV, and resilience; gradual load to avoid autonomic flare.

text: Wearable setup: please enable Garmin → Elyx sync. Baseline HRV 42 ms, avg sleep 6h 10m. Goal: +45m sleep over 4 weeks.
decision_rationale: Sleep extension should improve HRV and lipid profile via stress reduction.
